{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","author_sig":"{\"payload\": \"\", \"payloadType\": \"application/vnd.rebar.authorship.v1+json\", \"signatures\": [{\"keyid\": \"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d\", \"sig\": \"\"}]}","data":{"fields":{"description":"# Derive and enforce plan-material-pin health\n\n## Goal\nUse signed pins as the single related-material validity check across every attestation lifecycle consumer, while preserving safe rollout for existing projects.\n\n## Implementation\n- Add verify.enforce_plan_material_pins with default false and strict enabled-mode validation.\n- Own the nested DerivedPlanReviewHealth contract returned as health beside compute_plan_review_validity existing top-level {valid, reason, verdict}. It has pin_status exactly current, stale-pin-drift, stale-pin-missing, malformed-pin, or legacy-unpinned; enforced boolean; and targets: list[TargetPinDetail]. Aggregate target status by fixed severity malformed-pin > stale-pin-missing > stale-pin-drift > current; legacy-unpinned occurs only for a wholly unpinned manifest with an empty targets list. Child 5967 extends the same contract with phase_status and phase compatibility after it introduces the phase manifest format. TargetPinDetail is exactly {canonical_id: string, role: child|prerequisite, pinned_fingerprint: string, current_fingerprint: string|null, pin_status: current|stale-pin-drift|stale-pin-missing|malformed-pin}; legacy-unpinned has an empty targets list. Compare signed pins against current narrow material to populate it; all renderers consume this contract rather than duplicating strings.\n- When enabled, drift, malformed pins, or a deleted/missing pinned target invalidate the attestation. Archived targets remain readable. When disabled, report the same observations as advisory while valid remains true.\n- Treat a wholly unpinned legacy attestation as valid in either mode. Do not rewrite pins when configuration changes.\n- Define PlanValidityProfile with exactly DEFAULT and CLOSE. Extend the existing attest.compute_validity(attestation, ticket_state, kind, *, repo_root=None, profile=PlanValidityProfile.DEFAULT) without renaming or wrapping it. For kind=completion-verifier the profile is ignored and existing completion.py callers never parse pins. Migrate plan-review callers claim_gate_check, idempotent reuse, drift_refresh_candidate, re-sign, audit/health, and the close story to this same function. DEFAULT runs every existing check including code freshness; CLOSE runs the same checks except code freshness. Both apply configured pin validity, and child 5967 later adds phase compatibility to both. Before returning a refresh candidate, drift_refresh_candidate calls compute_validity(kind=plan-review, profile=DEFAULT); if returned valid is false it returns None before the probe. With enforcement enabled, stale-pin-drift, stale-pin-missing, and malformed-pin make valid=false; current and legacy-unpinned remain valid. With enforcement disabled, every pin_status remains valid and observable as advisory.\n- Keep optional unreadable configuration fail-open with a warning, matching existing gate posture; once enforcement is successfully enabled, validation fails closed.\n\n## Acceptance Criteria\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift invalidates the claim consumer.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift invalidates the close-profile consumer when that gate is active.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift prevents idempotent attestation reuse.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift prevents progressive drift refresh.\n- [ ] Enabled pin drift prevents re-sign.\n- [ ] Audit reports enabled pin drift as invalid.\n- [ ] Derived health reports enabled pin drift as invalid.\n- [ ] Disabled enforcement reports the same drift as advisory without changing valid.\n- [ ] Legacy unpinned attestations remain valid across configuration toggles.\n- [ ] verify.enforce_plan_material_pins=true leaves new pin emission enabled.\n- [ ] verify.enforce_plan_material_pins=false leaves new pin emission enabled.\n- [ ] Missing/deleted, archived, malformed, duplicate, and re-enable scenarios are deterministic.\n- [ ] No warning event is persisted for derived health.\n- [ ] Malformed manifest metadata returns malformed/invalid at every consumer without raising.\n\n## Verification\n- Run focused attestation invalidation, reuse, drift-refresh, re-sign, and config tests.\n- Run make check and the non-integration test suite.\n"}},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"EDIT","timestamp":1784538819852388001,"uuid":"d9b63eaf-9e2a-4b27-8d2d-e89b275bdf25"}